uhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aPolitical, economic and social barriers among Latin America, the Caribbean and Canada are giving way to global forces and the "global dreams" they inspire. This collection of original articles and essays examines popular culture, literature, theatre, belief systems, indigenous practices and questions of identity, exile and alienation. The interconnectedness and distinction of cultural production throughout the Americas, "transplanted" interests, the mediation of African and European influences, and the expression of shifting identities, all reflect the development of a new American neighbourhood.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Developing & Emerging Countries.2bisacsh1 aAlgoo-Baksh, Stella, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAllen, Carolyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAraújo, Nara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArratia, Maria-Inés, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAverill, Gage, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeaucage, Pierre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCase, Frederick Ivor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCharles, Embert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCiria, Alberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCraven, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCurtius, Anny Dominique, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEsteva, Gustavo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEtcheverry, Jorge, econtributor.